{"id": "EUVD-2022-55671", "enisaUuid": "bd7aed99-540c-355a-8b83-f42d187d66fd", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\npinctrl: thunderbay: fix possible memory leak in thunderbay_build_functions()\n\nThe thunderbay_add_functions() will free memory of thunderbay_funcs\nwhen everything is ok, but thunderbay_funcs will not be freed when\nthunderbay_add_functions() fails, then there will be a memory leak,\nso we need to add kfree() when thunderbay_add_functions() fails to\nfix it.\n\nIn addition, doing some cleaner works, moving kfree(funcs) from\nthunderbay_add_functions() to thunderbay_build_functions().", "datePublished": "2025-10-22T15:31:09", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-22T15:31:09", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3650943bab29d03ef147290451237713ed1942cd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/aae4846e8e49044cb51d0276bec2a3fc2d5cd8da", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/83e1bcaf8cef26edaaf2a6098ef760f563683483", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50557"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50557"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0b604e59-4858-3209-8cf7-9f0be33417a0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "12422af8194df85243d68b11f8783de9d01e58dc <83e1bcaf8cef26edaaf2a6098ef760f563683483"}, {"id": "5972f64c-eb2b-39e4-a15f-361c5cb83363", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.16"}, {"id": "597f657f-5171-38ce-85c6-2c000dd40ec5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.17"}, {"id": "5efe6651-b6af-3938-a657-02941424da95", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.2"}, {"id": "6a0acad7-fdaf-35e2-ab4c-b28ca1406b43", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2"}, {"id": "8aead4b4-2c3b-37e8-a52c-a319fa555727", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "9db56140-2649-386e-8b40-f5b0d9aa31e9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "12422af8194df85243d68b11f8783de9d